<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="403" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,682,1175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,682,707]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body short, slender. Palps well developed, completely or almost completely fused. Prostomium with 2 pairs of eyes, sometimes also with 1 pair of anterior eyespots, and 3 antennae. Peristomium with 1 pair of short, papilliform or ovate peristomial cirri. Compound chaetae as falcigers and, frequently, spiniger-like chaetae; falciger blades usually bidentate, subdistal tooth larger, blades partially fused to shafts or absent in some species; shafts of spiniger-like chaetae with triangular processes in some species. Dorsal simple chaetae present from anterior chaetigers, ventral simple chaetae usually only on posterior chaetigers. Aciculae commonly inflated distally, frequently hollow, with slightly curved tip. Pygidium with 1 pair of anal cirri, usually longer than dorsal cirri. Reproduction by epigamy, with ventral incubation of eggs and embryos.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="403" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,682,1175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,970,995]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[449,547,972,995]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[449,547,972,995]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Exogone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was revised by 
<bibRefCitation box="[733,942,971,995]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="San Martin, G. (1991) Grubeosyllis and Exogone (Exogoninae, Syllidae, Polychaeta) from Cuba, the Gulf of Mexico, Florida and Puerto Rico, with a revision of Exogone. Bulletin of Marine Science, 49 (3), 715 - 740." type="journal article">San Martín (1991)</bibRefCitation>
who established 3 sub-genera: 
<taxonomicName authority="Mesnil &amp; Caullery, 1918" authorityName="Mesnil &amp; Caullery" authorityYear="1918" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Parexogone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1301,1435,972,995]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Parexogone</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mesnil" box="[151,440,1006,1031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Mesnil, F. &amp; Caullery, M. (1918) Sur l'organisation et la biologie d'un Syllidien [Exogone (Parexogone, n. s. g.) hebes Webst. et Ben. var. hibernica South.] habitant un sable compact. Bulletin de la Societe Zoologique de France, 42 (Volume for 1917), 126 - 132." type="journal article" year="1918">Mesnil &amp; Caullery, 1918</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Orsted, 1845" authorityName="Orsted" authorityYear="1845" box="[454,709,1006,1031]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[454,552,1007,1030]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Exogone</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Orsted" box="[562,709,1006,1031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Orsted, A. S. (1845) Ueber die Entwicklung der Jungen bei einer Annelide und uber die ausseren Unterschiede zwischen beiden Geschlechtern. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 11 (1), 20 - 23." type="journal article" year="1845">Ørsted, 1845</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Claparede, 1864" authorityName="Claparede" authorityYear="1864" box="[770,1045,1006,1031]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sylline" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[770,846,1006,1031]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Sylline</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Claparede" box="[856,1045,1006,1031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Claparede, E. (1864) Glanures zootomiques parmi les annelides de Port-Vendres (Pyrenees Orientales). Memoires de la Societe de Physique d´Histoire Naturelle de Geneve, 17 (2), 463 - 600." type="journal article" year="1864">Claparède, 1864</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Boggemann" box="[1059,1436,1006,1031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Boggemann, M. &amp; Westheide, W. (2004) Interstitial Syllidae (Annelida: Polychaeta) from Mahe (Seychelles). Journal of Natural History, 38 (4), 403 - 446." type="journal article" year="2004">Böggemann &amp; Westheide (2004)</bibRefCitation>
raised 
<taxonomicName box="[232,366,1044,1067]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Parexogone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[232,366,1044,1067]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Parexogone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the generic level, and recent studies on the 
<taxonomicName box="[963,1055,1042,1067]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Annelida" rank="family">Syllidae</taxonomicName>
have abandoned the subgenera classification, considering 
<taxonomicName box="[451,549,1079,1102]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[451,549,1079,1102]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Exogone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as monophyletic and not recognizing 
<emphasis box="[977,994,1079,1102]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">E</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName box="[1018,1116,1079,1102]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Exogone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1018,1116,1079,1102]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Exogone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<emphasis box="[1180,1197,1079,1102]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">E</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName authority="Claparède, 1864" authorityName="Claparède" authorityYear="1864" box="[1221,1297,1078,1103]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Sylline" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1221,1297,1078,1103]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Sylline</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as separate subgenera (Aguado &amp; San Martín 2009; 
<bibRefCitation author="Aguado" box="[612,832,1114,1139]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Aguado, M. T., San Martin, G. &amp; Siddall, M. E. (2012) Systematics and evolution of syllids (Annelida, Syllidae). Cladistics, 28, 234 - 250." type="journal article" year="2012">
Aguado 
<emphasis box="[708,765,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Paresque" box="[844,1078,1114,1139]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Paresque, K., Fukuda, M. V. &amp; Nogueira, J. M. M. (2014) The genus Exogone (Polychaeta: Syllidae) from the Brazilian coast, with the description of a new species. Zootaxa, 3790 (4), 501 - 533." type="journal article" year="2014">
Paresque 
<emphasis box="[953,1002,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
). This classification is followed herein.
</paragraph>
